snippet.textDisplay:
Hearing Hashim Mahmud’s voice, Imon Bhai’s music together is truly soul-stirring. Once you listen, you can’t stop.

Back in the day, songs used to come alive in the fairs; now Hashim Mahmud is receiving the recognition he deserves while still alive. That 3:21 mark—what energy in the voice!

Coke Studio Bangla has beautifully showcased our rich culture to the world. Heartfelt respect to the entire team for bringing Hashim Mahmud’s masterpiece back to life. Hopefully, many more such creative songs will follow. 🥰🥰

Emon very poorly portraited the song, he could've done much better - we know he is far more capable. The weight of this song deserves more solid instrumental work. By the way, intro set the bar high, but disappointed end of the song eventually, except the Hashim Mahmud entry.
